# Normalize line endings — the repo is authored with LF; without this, every
# git operation on Windows checkouts warns "LF will be replaced by CRLF".
# `text=auto eol=lf` stores text files with LF in the repo and checks them out
# with LF everywhere, killing the churn/warnings.
* text=auto eol=lf

# Scripts must stay LF regardless of platform (bash/hook shims break on CRLF).
*.sh text eol=lf
bin/astramem text eol=lf

# Explicit binaries — never touch these.
*.png binary
*.jpg binary
*.gif binary
*.ico binary
*.woff binary
*.woff2 binary
